text: Vedas Venkaiah (Telugu:వెదస్ వెంకయ్య)(born 2 March 1941) is an Indian politician and former Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) for Suryapet Assembly Constituency under the Indian National Congress party between 2004-2009.

Byreddy Rajasekhar Reddy (born 1954) is an Indian politician and founder of Rayalaseema Parirakshana Samithi, for separate statehood for Rayalaseema region of Andhra Pradesh. He is fighting for rights of people of Rayalaseema, and was opposed to the formation of Rayala Telangana.

Tula Uma (Telugu: తుల ఉమ), born 25 December 1970 is the first woman ZP chairperson of Karimnagar District and the state mahila president of the Telangana Rashtra Samithi, a Regional Party in India. She is a ZPTC from the Kathalapur mandal of Karimnagar District, Telangana. She took oath in the coveted ZP chairperson position on 5 July 2014

Dr. Ashok Kumar (Hindi: अशोक कुमार, born 08 December 1948) is an Indian politician. His political party is the Indian National Congress. He is a Member of Legislative Assembly where he represents Singhia constituency, he has represented the constituency for five terms. Dr. Kumar has an MBBS from Patna Medical College and Hospital.
